Key Match Events: The Milwaukee Brewers clinched the NL Central before their game against the Philadelphia Phillies even began.
The Brewers celebrated a 2-1 walkoff win over the Philadelphia Phillies.
Post-Match Reflections: Team manager Pat Murphy honored Bob Uecker as 'epitomizing a champion' during the celebration.
Bob Uecker was celebrated by the Brewers players and coaches after their victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Brewers clinched their third division title in four years.
Bob Uecker, a legendary broadcaster and former catcher, was a central figure in the celebration.
